        "title" : null,
        "hasTitle" : false,
        "message" : [
          "%script",
          "-- confirm that Select AI interacts with the GenAI LLM service",
          "SELECT AI chat \"In two sentences, explain what Oracle OCI is\";"
        ],
        "selectedVisualization" : "raw",
        "visualizationConfig" : null,
        "hideCode" : true,
        "hideResult" : true,
        "hideGutter" : true,
        "hideVizConfig" : true,
        "hideInIFrame" : false,
        "enabled" : true,
        "forms" : "[]",
        "result" : {
          "startTime" : 1744145268369,
          "endTime" : 1744145272149,
          "interpreter" : "script.low",
          "taskStatus" : "SUCCESS",
          "status" : "SUCCESS",
          "results" : [
            {
              "message" : "RESPONSE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              \nOracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) is a comprehensive cloud platform that provides a wide range of services, including computing, storage, networking, and database management, to support the deployment of enterprise-level applications and workloads. With OCI, users can build, deploy, and manage modern cloud-native applications, as well as migrate and run traditional enterprise workloads, all while taking advantage of Oracle's high-performance, secure, and scalable infrastructure.   \n\n\n\n---------------------------\n",
              "type" : "TEXT"
            }
          ],
          "forms" : "[]"
        },
        "relations" : [ ],
        "dynamicFormParams" : "{}"
      },
      {
        "row" : 0,
        "col" : 0,
        "sizeX" : 0,
        "width" : 12,
        "title" : null,
        "hasTitle" : false,
        "message" : [
          "%script",
          "--use Select AI RAG to ask about a Sherlock Holmes story",
          "SELECT AI NARRATE",
          "\"who stole the blue carbuncle?\";"
        ],
        "selectedVisualization" : "raw",
        "visualizationConfig" : null,
        "hideCode" : false,
        "hideResult" : false,
        "hideGutter" : true,
        "hideVizConfig" : false,
        "hideInIFrame" : false,
        "enabled" : true,
        "forms" : "[]",
        "result" : {
          "startTime" : 1749760525700,
          "endTime" : 1749760530644,
          "interpreter" : "script.low",
          "taskStatus" : "SUCCESS",
          "status" : "SUCCESS",
          "results" : [
            {
              "message" : "\nRESPONSE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \nThe blue carbuncle was stolen by James Ryder, the upper-attendant at the Hotel Cosmopolitan, not John Horner, the plumber, who was initially accused of the crime. Ryder's guilt was revealed by Sherlock Holmes, who solved the case.\n\nSources:\n  - sherlock_holmes.txt (https://objectstorage.us-chicago-1.oraclecloud.com/n/orasenatdpltintegration03/b/JoeHahnRagBucket/o/rag/doc/sherlock_holmes.txt)    \n\n\n---------------------------\n",
              "type" : "TEXT"
            }
          ],
          "forms" : "[]"
        },
        "relations" : [ ],
        "dynamicFormParams" : "{}"
      },
      {
        "row" : 0,
        "col" : 0,
        "sizeX" : 0,
        "width" : 12,
        "title" : null,
        "hasTitle" : false,
        "message" : [
          "%script",
          "--ask about Great Gatsby",
          "SELECT AI NARRATE",
          "\"who does Jay Gatsby love?\";"
        ],
        "selectedVisualization" : "raw",
        "visualizationConfig" : null,
        "hideCode" : false,
        "hideResult" : false,
        "hideGutter" : true,
        "hideVizConfig" : false,
        "hideInIFrame" : false,
        "enabled" : true,
        "forms" : "[]",
        "result" : {
          "startTime" : 1749760691114,
          "endTime" : 1749760696159,
          "interpreter" : "script.low",
          "taskStatus" : "SUCCESS",
          "status" : "SUCCESS",
          "results" : [
            {
              "message" : "\nRESPONSE                                                                                                                                                                               \nJay Gatsby loves Daisy. He is overwhelmingly aware of her youth and mystery, and he feels married to her. He insists that Daisy loves him too, and he wants to speak to her alone. \n\nSources:\n  - great_gatsby.txt (https://objectstorage.us-chicago-1.oraclecloud.com/n/orasenatdpltintegration03/b/JoeHahnRagBucket/o/rag/doc/great_gatsby.txt)    \n\n\n---------------------------\n",
              "type" : "TEXT"
            }
          ],
          "forms" : "[]"
        },
        "relations" : [ ],
        "dynamicFormParams" : "{}"
      },
      {
        "row" : 0,
        "col" : 0,
        "sizeX" : 0,
        "width" : 12,
        "title" : null,
        "hasTitle" : false,
        "message" : [
          "%script",
          "--ask a Wuthering Heights question",
          "SELECT AI NARRATE",
          "\"who does Heathcliff fight with?\";"
        ],
        "selectedVisualization" : "raw",
        "visualizationConfig" : null,
        "hideCode" : false,
        "hideResult" : false,
        "hideGutter" : true,
        "hideVizConfig" : false,
        "hideInIFrame" : false,
        "enabled" : true,
        "forms" : "[]",
        "result" : {
          "startTime" : 1749760719292,
          "endTime" : 1749760719851,
          "interpreter" : "script.low",
          "taskStatus" : "SUCCESS",
          "status" : "SUCCESS",
          "results" : [
            {
              "message" : "\nRESPONSE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \nHeathcliff fights with Hindley and also has a confrontation with Edgar Linton. In one instance, Hindley knocks Heathcliff under the feet of a horse, and in another, Heathcliff threatens to fight Edgar Linton, but is deterred by Catherine, who warns him that Edgar will return with pistols and assistants.\n\nSources:\n  - wuthering_heights.txt (https://objectstorage.us-chicago-1.oraclecloud.com/n/orasenatdpltintegration03/b/JoeHahnRagBucket/o/rag/doc/wuthering_heights.txt)    \n\n\n---------------------------\n",
              "type" : "TEXT"
            }
          ],
          "forms" : "[]"
        },
        "relations" : [ ],
        "dynamicFormParams" : "{}"
      },
