            {
              "message" : "\nRESPONSE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \nAccording to Charles Dickens' classic novel \"A Christmas Carol\", Ebenezer Scrooge thinks that Christmas is a \"humbug\". He believes it to be a waste of time and money, and that people only pretend to be merry and charitable during the holiday season in order to appear virtuous. Scrooge is a miserly and bitter old man who has no use for the joy, kindness, and generosity that Christmas represents. He would much rather be left alone to focus on his business and accumulate wealth, and sees no value in the festive spirit or the idea of giving to others.    \n\n\n---------------------------\n",
